com.thomsonreuters.ema.access

Interface AckMsg

  • All Superinterfaces:
    ComplexType, Data, Msg

    public interface AckMsg
extends Msg
    AckMsg indicates success or failure of PostMsg.

    If requested, AckMsg is sent by provider acting on PostMsg received from consumer. AckMsg indicates success or failure of caching / processing of received PostMsg.

    AckMsg is optional. Consumer requests provider to send AckMsg by calling PostMsg.solicitAck(boolean) with true.
